<P>
 I innocently began to read "The Twilight Zone" (by Patt Morrison, April 24) on 
my way to the crossword puzzle and unexpectedly bumped into some implied ethnic 
slurs and geographical sour grapes. Calling Steven Spielberg cheap and 
minimizing New York City's entertainment resources by implying that they are 
limited to three other prominent Jewish males was nicely offset by three 
anti-American digs. 
</P>
<P>
 If taking swipes is the thing to do, how about finding a new angle instead of 
using the same tired old stereotypes? 
</P>
<P>
 DEBORAH OPENDEN 
</P>
