<P>
AN L.A. FLAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Peter Deep's letter (April 17) referring to California being called 
the state for "fruits and nuts" as "California bashing" with a "subtle anti-gay 
message" (L.A. Speak, Palm Latitudes, March 30): That joke has been around for 
about 50 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Why can't people laugh anymore? I may not be a fruit, but I am a 71-year-old 
California-born nut; I may even be a flake and am proud of it. 
</P>
<P>
 Why is there so much resentment? Why can't you pass someone in the grocery 
store and smile and nod? Who cares who or what they are? 
</P>
<P>
 And they might smile back at you -- and surely make your day. 
</P>
<P>
 BETTE A. DUPUIS 
</P>
<P>
 Los Osos 
</P>
