<P>
 SEASONS OF THE COYOTE edited by Philip L. Harrison (Tehabi/Harper Collins 
West: $24.95; 114 pp., paperback original). Intelligent, adaptable and 
persistent, the coyote inhabits virtually every corner of North America, 
despite ill-advised campaigns to exterminate it. The brief essays is this 
attractive volume extol the cleverness and scroungy beauty of the coyote, and 
recap the important place it occupies in Native American mythologies. 
</P>
