</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE WATCH by Rick Bass (Norton: $9.95; 190 pp.). Rick Bass' short stories have 
a quirky tone that distinguishes them from his more straightforward 
reportage.Unable to find a place in contemporary America, his characters gamely 
limp through life, despite physical and psychological afflictions. The 
crotchety narrator of "The Government Bears" sums up their attitude when he 
concludes, "There's a lady three miles down the road who handles snakes in her 
church services and I swear that takes less courage than to just duck your head 
and keep on doing what you are doing, the regular." 
</P>
