<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALM LATITUDES: L.A. SPEAK; MOVIE POSTER PARLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Suzy Beal 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 bang: n. exclamation point. "That ad line looks a little dull.Let's stick a 
bang on it to dress it up." 
</P>
<P>
 ghost: v . to superimpose art or type onto something else. "We ghosted the 
headline over his stomach. It helps hide that awful shirt." 
</P>
<P>
 he's-a/she's-a: n. cliched A+B=C ad copy. " He's a beautician. She's a cop. 
Together, they're 'Deadly Beauty.' " 
</P>
<P>
 s&m: n. a formal presentation; for "stand and model." "Fox didn't just want to 
see the layout; I had to do an s&m for them." 
</P>
<P>
 Slim Fast: n. photo crop that trims an actor's unsightly bulges. Syn. 
knife-o-suction. 
</P>
<P>
 wild posting: v . covering buildings, construction sites, etc., with posters 
to start off an ad campaign. Suzy Beal 
</P>
</TEXT>
