himself as the modern inheritor of the '70s outlaw movement may make for good 
copy, but truth is, Tritt fits as squarely within the mainstream nowadays as 
his frequent target Billy Ray Cyrus.He's still reasonably charming, if not 
nearly charming enough to justify the ego. Tritt's choice of weepers ranges 
from cloying to clever; he's better as an exceedingly frisky Southern rocker, 
his preferred performance mode. 
