<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEIDI SIEGMUND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** Nas, "illmatic," Columbia. In an obvious attempt to wrestle hip-hop away 
from the West, East Coast critics have been gushing over Long Island's Nas as 
if he were rap's second coming.Don't believe the hype. While "The World Is 
Yours" is one of the year's smartest, silkiest numbers and his delivery is 
equally smooth, too much of the album is mired with tired attitudes and 
posturing. 
</P>
