<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; SPACED OUT AFTER 25 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is the 25th anniversary of the first moon landing and the Apollo space 
program.In commemoration, "Celebration 25: Man on the Moon," at the Space 
Center Houston, continues through Labor Day with special anniversary 
attractions. 
</P>
<P>
 "Spaceweek," July 16-24, will be a national anniversary celebration with 
astronaut appearances and a "Lunar Laser Spectacular" re-creating the moon 
landing. Admission to the center, 22 miles from Houston at Johnson Space 
Center, is $11.95, $8.50 for ages 3 to 11 and $10.75 for those 65 and over. 
Information: (800) 972-0369. 
</P>
