<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; NEW BUYING GUIDE FOR TRAVELERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When buying a big-ticket item, such as a refrigerator or a car, many people 
consult Consumer Reports magazine or buying guide. Now, the editors of those 
staples of consumerism have come out with a guide to vacation spending -- the 
new "Consumer Reports Travel Buying Guide 1994." Subtitled "How to get big 
discounts on air fares, hotels, car rentals and more," the annual guide sells 
for $8.99 in local bookstores. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA052294-0080 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 044071 </DOCID>
