<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAST WORD ON JULIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The next time you go to Julian ("Weekend Escape," April 10), don't go through 
Escondido. Continue on (California Highway) 78 and follow the Wild Animal Park 
signs.This will take you onto a two-lane road that goes through lovely country 
and past the ostrich farm. You can make a right on a small asphalt road which 
will bring you out west of the San Pasqual history center, or continue another 
half-mile to hook up with 78 by the animal park. It's easier and prettier. 
</P>
<P>
 Julian is not a center of gourmet dining, but the Julian Cafe has a pretty 
fair chicken pot pie, a great barbecue sandwich and a super hamburger. The 
Italian restaurant behind the cider mill isn't bad either. And don't forget to 
try the old-fashioned malts at the local drug store -- $2.50, but enough for 
two. For the best apple pie it's Farmer's Market in Wynola. 
</P>
<P>
 And don't go (to Julian) on Monday or Tuesday if you're a shopper; most stores 
are closed. 
</P>
<P>
 PEGGY JO HIMMELBERG, Dana Point 
</P>
</TEXT>
