<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP; FONTANA ENDS BELL GARDENS' SEASON IN A SLUGFEST, 14-8 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY CHAVEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The roof caved in on Bell Gardens when Fontana scored eight runs in the fourth 
en route to a 14-8 Southern Section Division I victory Friday at Veterans 
Stadium in the City of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers led 2-0 on consecutive squeeze bunts by Bill Barajas and Alex 
Castillo in the third inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Fontana responded with eight runs off Barajas in the fourth, led by Paul 
Orabona's bases-loaded triple. Orabona went three for four with four runs 
batted in. Four of Fontana's runs in the inning were unearned. 
</P>
<P>
 Pete Loza relieved Barajas in the fifth after Barajas had given up 11 runs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers mounted a small comeback with one run in the fourth and two runs 
in the fifth. With the bases loaded in the sixth, Loza drove in a run on a 
fielder's choice at second. The Lancers scored again on a passed ball. Manuel 
Aranas' single drove in the third run to make the score 14-8, but he was thrown 
out at second trying to stretch the hit into a double. 
</P>
<P>
 Aranas was two for four with two RBIs. GARY CHAVEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
