<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LATEEL FRIERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cantwell-Sacred Heart 8, Cathedral 3 -- Pitchers Christian Hernandez and Ray 
Nuno combined for a two-hitter, and Manny Ciallo had a two-run double to give 
Cantwell-Sacred Heart an upset win Friday in the first round of the Southern 
Section Division IV playoffs at Jackie Robinson Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Phantoms carried an eight-game winning streak and hope to use that 
momentum into the game, but appeared flat after falling behind 3-0 in the 
second inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez (5-2) struck out 10 and limited Cathedral to two hits in six 
innings. Nuno retired three of the last four batters. 
</P>
<P>
 Luis DeLeon had a triple to center field in fourth and Manny Badillo had a 
single in the fifth for Cathedral's only hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Phantom right-hander Greg Vidales pitched four innings, giving up six runs 
(five earned) on eight hits and three walks. 
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't play our type of game," Cathedral Coach Robert Morales said. "Our 
players were preoccupied with tonight's school prom." LATEEL FRIERSON 
