<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKFISH RECOVER, NOW FACE ANGLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Conservation efforts from Maine to Floria have brought the rockfish back from 
near extinction, a federal commission said. 
</P>
<P>
 In declaring the rockfish recovered, the Atlantic States Marine Fisheries 
Commission cleared the way for relaxing catch restrictions that have protected 
the species since the early 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
