<TEXT>
<P>
 A group of young men who tried to crash a birthday party in Thousand Oaks may 
have fired four gunshots into a truck parked in the driveway after being asked 
to leave, law enforcement officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies answered a call of a large party disturbing 
the peace 1200 block of Sheffield Place about 9:30 p.m. Friday.Witnesses told 
deputies that three men tried to crash the party and shouted what they believed 
to be gang slogans. 
</P>
<P>
 "Apparently the people asked to leave had some gang affiliations," Sgt. Terry 
Hughes said. The party hosts said they thought the men threw some firecrackers 
and left. But about 9:30 a.m. Saturday, deputies were called back to the 
Thousand Oaks house after the resident found four bullet holes in his truck. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's officials suspect that what the witnesses thought were firecrackers 
were actually gunshots. TRACY WILSON 
