<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE STATE SOFTBALL PLAYOFFS; LONG BEACH USES DOUBLE STEAL TO OUST 
CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress College's bid for the State softball championship ended Saturday night 
when the Chargers were defeated, 1-0, by Long Beach in the double-elimination 
tournament in Visalia. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach (40-6) scored the game's only run with a double steal in the second 
inning.With runners at the corners, the runner on first broke for second and 
drew the throw. Brenda Rogers, who had reached base on an error, then scored 
from third. 
</P>
<P>
 After an 18-inning loss Friday night to College of the Sequoias, Cypress 
stayed alive for two games Saturday behind the pitching of freshman Jenny 
Lopez. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers shut out Fresno, 3-0, behind Lopez and Jackie Ruiz, who relieved 
in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (45-17) scored one run in the fourth inning and two in the sixth, and 
all three runs came with two outs and as the result of errors. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress then defeated San Joaquin Delta, 1-0, in 10 innings when Briana 
Yoshina drew a two-out, bases-loaded walk. 
</P>
