<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIORDAN TO SPEAK AT ASIAN PACIFIC AWARDS DINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mayor Richard Riordan is scheduled to toast the final week of Asian Pacific 
American Heritage Month on Tuesday at a dinner celebrating the family unit, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The mayor is going to be basically doing the welcoming remarks since he is 
the honorary chair of Asian Pacific American Heritage Month this year," said 
Lorain Wong, co-chairwoman of the event. 
</P>
<P>
 The 16th annual dinner, sponsored by AT&T and Kaiser Permanente, will begin at 
7 p.m. Tuesday in the California Ballroom of the Westin Bonaventure Hotel, 404 
S. Figueroa St. 
</P>
<P>
 In honor of this year's theme, "Celebrating the Family -- The Foundation of 
Our Future," the organizing committee will present 10 awards to individuals and 
community groups. 
</P>
<P>
 Honorees include Philip Vera Cruz, former vice president of the United Farm 
Workers Union; Joe Hicks, executive director of the Southern Christian 
Leadership Conference; Dr. Indong Oh, former chairman of the Korean American 
Coalition, as well as the Gay Asian Pacific Support Network and the Los Angeles 
Asian Pacific Islander Sisters -- two gay and lesbian support groups. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $50. Information: (213) 353-6050. 
</P>
