<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: SOUTH GATE; GRANT WILL PAY TO ADD 2 NEW OFFICERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Police Department has been awarded a $200,000 federal grant to add two 
officers to its 91-member force for the next three years. 
</P>
<P>
 The Department of Justice Police Supplement Hiring Grant will pay half the 
salary and benefits of the officers. The city will match the grant money with 
asset seizure funds. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers will be assigned to the city's crime-impact team, a component of 
the department's new community-based policing program. 
</P>
