<P>
SANTA ANA MAN KILLED DURING SEARCH FOR PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old Santa Ana man was shot and killed while searching for a party 
Saturday morning, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Edgar Zazueta and a friend were invited to an after-hours party in an 
apartment complex at 2111 W. 17th St., Santa Ana police Officer Joseph Williams 
said. The pair was driving around the building about 3 a.m. attempting to 
locate the party when a lone gunman confronted them, Williams said. 
</P>
<P>
 After a short conversation, the gunman shot Zazueta in the head and fled on 
foot, Williams said. It was not known why Zazueta was shot or whether any 
weapons were recovered, Williams said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police had no information on Zazueta's unidentified passenger and no 
description of the gunman. 
