<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: HANCOCK HAS PERFECT NIGHT AT VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNEDY COSGROVE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Greg Hancock, 23, of Costa Mesa, won all five of his four-lap heats to finish 
first with a perfect score of 15 points in the American Speedway Motorcycle 
Finals at Ventura Raceway Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Hancock was one of five members of the defending World Team Cup champions, 
along with Billy Hamill, Josh Larsen, Dukie Ermolenko and Chris Manchester. 
</P>
<P>
 First place was pretty much decided in the fourth round, when Hancock, Larsen 
and Manchester faced off in a heat race and finished in that order. 
</P>
<P>
 The top five finishers earned berths in the overseas qualifier -- the final 
stepping stone to the World Championships -- and Hamill and Manchester were 
tied for third coming into the fifth round while Ermolenko was tied for fifth 
with Mike Faria and Charlie Venegas. Baseball  
</P>
<P>
 Former Crescenta Valley High baseball player Brendon Cowsill has signed with 
the Angels. Cowsill, drafted by the Angels last June, played for L.A. City 
College this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowsill, who also played basketball for Crescenta Valley, was drafted in the 
34th round. The 6-foot-3, 175-pound third baseman will play for Mesa (Ariz.) in 
the Rookie League starting in June. Volleyball  
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake High volleyball player Matt Sebree has been extended an 
invitation to try out for the U.S. Olympic Festival in St. Louis in July. 
KENNEDY COSGROVE 
</P>
