<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME SALES CONTINUE STRONG IN APRIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Special to The Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southland home sales continued strong in April despite the recent increases in 
mortgage interest rates. A total of 18,378 new and used houses and condos were 
sold last month, down 6% from 19,557 in March and up 18.9% from April last year 
when 15,459 homes were sold, according to Dataquick Information Systems. 
</P>
<P>
 Prices have continued to decline in all counties except San Diego and 
Riverside. Southland Home Sales 07,16,10,10,07,09,09,07 No. Sold No. Sold Pct. 
